# Phase 02: ApiVersions Truth

## Date
2026-05-02

## Phase File
tips/phases/02-api-versions-truth.md

## Intent
Harden Tansu's API versioning to strictly adhere to "no advertised API without proof". Ensure that `tansu-service` rejects any request versions outside the explicitly approved ranges by responding with `ErrorCode::UnsupportedVersion` (35), synthesized as correctly typed protocol responses.

## Files Touched
- `tansu-service/src/api.rs`
- `tansu-broker/tests/compatibility_contract.rs`
- `phase-logs/index.json`
- `phase-logs/02-api-versions-truth.md.log`

## Ledger Rows Touched
N/A (No new ledger rows added, but bounded execution enforced for all APIs)

## Tests Added
- `tansu-broker/tests/compatibility_contract.rs::broker_rejects_unsupported_request_versions`

## Verification Commands
- `cargo test -p tansu-broker --test compatibility_contract`
- `cargo check -p tansu-service -p tansu-broker`
- `cargo fmt --all`

## Outcomes
`FrameRouteService` now compares every incoming request against `advertised_versions`. If out of bounds, it intercepts the request and generates a strongly-typed API response frame mapped with `ErrorCode::UnsupportedVersion` (code 35). `ApiVersionsRequest` bypasses this bounds-checking because it safely handles unsupported versions internally to correctly return its API boundaries. E2E tests confirm that out-of-bounds versions are correctly intercepted and properly serialized.

## Residual Risks
None.
